The Pink Ladies have confirmed that the missing Strand mother and her infant have been found. CAPE TOWN - The Pink Ladies have confirmed that the missing Strand mother and her infant have been found alive.Bianca Jackson and with her son Joshua went missing on Thursday night after leaving the Asara Wine Estate in Stellenbosch. It's understood her phone battery died as she was making her way home.The Pink Ladies' Dessie Rechner says: We re absolutely delighted to tell you that Bianca and her son have been found alive on the Drakenstein Mountain. The mother and child have been taken in for check-up. No further details on the matter were provided.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)